Collaborating For a Forest Based Bioeconomy

Author

Philipp Jonas Kreutzer

Published

April 28, 2025

The network below is based on SWINNO data covering innovations commercialized between 1970 and 2021.

The nodes are firms and organizations aggregated to the best of our knowledge into their most representative parent organization. Their color indicates the share of their innovations that belong to the forest-based bioeconomy. Nodes with 0% bioeconomy share are rendered in blue, those with 100% in dark green. Their size corresponds to the total number of innovations commercialized by the firms between 1970 and 2021.

Links represent commercialized innovations on which at least two companies collaborated. Their color indicates if the innovation belonged to the bioeconomy (green), or not (gray).

Forest-bioeconomy innovation is defined as any innovation which either due to the origin or use sector relates to forestry, or makes use of a forest derived product.

By clicking on a node additional information is available about the firms’ innovation experience.
